$interpreted: Maria: Master Clark, why are they so mad? I don't understand. Do they not like me?
Clark: ...You still don't understand what you've done, do you?
Clark: You beat the living daylights out of them. Of course they don't like you.
Maria: But...Maria's settings are such that I must obey my user's commands.
Maria: Sooo, follow Master Clark's orders now and say sorry to them.
Clark: You're not really sorry...
Clark: Is that other man also your user?
Clark: He told you to attack me, even to kill me. Why didn't you obey his commands?
Maria: Clark fixed Maria, so Maria doesn't want to kill Clark.
Clark: You see, your settings allow you to make your own decision at times.
Maria: ...Maria...doesn't understand...
Clark: It must be too complicated for you at this time...
Mr. Waits: Maria!
Clark: You again...*sigh*...
Mr. Waits: Maria! Come here, I'm your real master!
Clark: Maria, don't you go over there!
Maria: Mr. Waits...Clark...Master...
Clark: You...!
Mr. Waits: Maria, you can't move! If you make even the slightest movement, I'll kill him!
Mr. Waits: Hmph! Maria only needs one master. If Maria doesn't move, I'll take care of you myself!
Clark: Maria!
Maria: ......
Clark: Do you remember what I just told you?
Maria: Maria's settings...Maria...analyzing commands...
Maria: Maria is differentiating...
Mr. Waits: Time to die!
Clark: Why are you so set on having Maria? All for a robot?
Mr. Waits: *cough*...*clears throat*...B-B-Before, while I was in the Desert Bazaar, I met a mechanical merchant named Sherlock...
Clark: (Sherlock...? Could that be the robot that the professor at the Academy had mentioned...?)
Mr. Waits: Maria is...much more advanced than him. Her power is immense...she must be worth a fortune...
Mr. Waits: So...no matter what it takes...I must have her...
Clark: Ah, yes. Money...
Mr. Waits: Hehe. This kind of mesmerizing killing machine...who wouldn't want it?
Maria: Sher...lock...
Clark: Maria?
Maria: A portion of the Main Core is damaged. A portion of the Main Core is damaged.
Clark: Maria, are you awake?
Maria: Master Clark! Awaiting command!
Clark: Luckily, you were just a little overheated. No need to restart...
Maria: Overheated? Maria isn't hot.
Clark: When you heard the word "Sherlock" your system froze.
Maria: Sherlock? Who's Sherlock?
Clark: Huh? That's strange...looks like we'd better make it to the Mechanical Territory as fast as possible...
Maria: Ooo! The Mechanical Territory! Maria wants to go!
Clark: But you spent all my travel expenses...
Clark: Looks like I'm going to have to work even harder these next few days. *sigh*...what a drag...
Maria: Maria can help Clark!
Clark: Eh...more of a hindrance than a help. Well, maybe...
Clark: No, no, no. No "maybe".
Clark: (I can't always be this overprotective. I'd better rethink this...)
Clark: If I let you interact with more people, it ought to give you more common sense...
Maria: Maria does not understand. But I will try my best!
Clark: Wonderful. After all, one day we won't be together anymore.
Clark: Before that day comes, I must make sure that you will not be a burden on others.
Maria: Maria will never leave Master Clark!
Maria: Maria will stay with Master Clark forever!
Clark: Terrible...I'm going to be suffocated to death...
Maria: It's Chu Chu! Oh, Chu Chu~Maria has "mixed" you so much! Chu Chu will be with Maria forever!
